content_vision: I survived while others did not. Surreal and metaphorical song. I'm floating in a small boat somewhere.
text:
Verse 1:
pray tomorrow takes me higher, no cap,
and that green that we roll up won't overlap.
if you with me, you gon eat, that's for sure,
and it was twenty years ago, life was pure.
life's just a joke, it's all just a game,
shit is just a satire, we'll laugh and take the blame.
we're all in this together, when you climb in,
down there, in the depths, we'll have a good time, it's not a sin.

Pre-Chorus 1:
in this hot desert land, you gotta stay alive
hop in a benz, take a ride, rev that engine, thrive.

Chorus 1:
we pour up, do another round,
but this life we live, it's just so sad man.
no sesame seeds, i'm allergic to that mess,
but thinkin' 'bout what i could have been, i must confess.

Verse 2:
you never listen to me then the call drop, hmmm
but i'll show you anyway, i got it all day, just all white like some weighed raw.
lend me your ears, i'll give you a piece of my mind,
let me tell you now, we'll leave the past behind.
i'm like a one- man show, i got it all day
cold heart cash only, i stash it away
and when i need to, i back it up, pave the way.
i see you lookin', rita, but you know what's up,

Pre-Chorus 2:
that nigga a real one, never been a fake,
but nowadays we're just consumers, always on the take,

Chorus 2:
can you break out of this bubble, see what's real,
but y'all just swim in circles, never really trying to feel.
this is the life for me now, no turning back,
my way of thinking, i don't retain less, stay on track.

Bridge:
i don't need no drama, it's just useless,
a double t means we keep it real all day, no bs.
she think she psyching, but it's all just a ploy,
it's hard to believe that she's playing with my boys,

don't judge me by my skin, don't judge me by my complexion,

know the fuck up, and you wait,
our love is like a ticking time bomb, can't escape.

Verse 2:
can't take the time to stop, keepin' up the pace
not the soul to slow me down, gotta win this race.

but the lies and betrayal, it still hurt just the same,
we're all going through it, playing this game.

Chorus 2:
slangin', keepin' it low key,
nigga get checked if they tryna step to me,
ah ah ah ah ah ah, no fuckin' way.
i stay up out the mix, mind my own business,

Bridge:
my youngins shoot like thunder, they don't play,
and you can't save hoes, they just gotta go away.
i'm a sucker for pain, and you're the flame,
burning me alive, i'm in shame.

Outro:
we laughed out loud, feelin' so carefree,
got nobody left to believe, just you and me.

Intro:
and when the wind blows like a lover's touch,
we hear it sigh and dee, it knows just how to move us.

Verse 1:
life's full of things we love to hate,
but we all gotta live through the pain,
knocking on death's door, that's just the game.
we got passion for the art, for the sound,
so why you hatin' on us, tryna bring us down?
just back it up, girl, move that thing,
look at me, baby, through it all, cling.
we back up in this bitch again, no surprise,

Pre-Chorus 1:
tell me you want me, i'll do anything you ask,
if you can make it here, i'll make sure it lasts,

Chorus 1:
hey kid, could you buy me a drink?
people try to say i'm acting funny, but i just think.
no one else will ever understand your tale,
but my name is rihanna, let me prevail.

Verse 2:
you know i'm a hitter, i'll knock you out quick
bitch, why you sleepin', no time to be sick
my heart goes boum boum boum boum boum, can't handle the stick.
i told them niggas, don't come for my crown,
you told me that you needed distance, but you always comin' around.

Pre-Chorus 2:
just like cryptolite, i'll light up your night,
tell me you want me and i'll make it right.

Chorus 2:
we used to have big dreams, reach for the sky,
but now we're just speedballing, don't know why.
angry at the world, can't blame me, it's no mystery,
gotta chase after that fast money, no room for hesitation or mystery.

Bridge:
you spin me right round, baby
take it now, don't slow down, maybe.
i'm tired of him always cheatin, it's too much to bear,
but i still need one more chance, baby i swear.

Outro:
change is coming and it's gonna do me good,
when i was in your shoes, misunderstood,

Instrumental:
i never gave a shit bout no messy bitch, she ain't worth my time,
but that hoe bring it back, she's got me committing the crime,

Intro:
all of that shit that you rap about, it's played out,
just be real, like that of one who knows what love's about.

Verse 1:
right now is the last time, we're gonna make it count,
godzillaembed, we're taking over, never slowing down.
'cause when we roll up in the club, it's finna get lit,
gonna start the night off right, forgettin' all the bullshit.

but i'll keep my promise, won't let it be undone,
live for today, you ain't gotta die, my son.
you can never walk like me, got my own swag,

Pre-Chorus 1:
if things keep going wrong, my life's gonna be fucked,
lord, if i could just get one more chance, i'd be outta luck.

Chorus 1:

everything i do is righteous, you know i'm serious.
life goes on, ain't gotta think about them,
it's all about living in the moment, you should join in.

Pre-Chorus 2:

Chorus 2:
who hov inspires, i'm on my own wave,
you told me that you needed distance, but it's all the same.

Outro:
with every step i take, my maneuver's on point,
and the shadows grew, but i won't disappoint.

Intro:
you electrify me, girl you got that spark,
all eyes on me, like i'm the one controlling the arc.

give me one more chance to make it right,
'cause if they catch me, i'll be locked up at night,
but all i need is your love to feel alright.

but they'll catch me soon and put me in a cell,
all i have left is this love, my saving grace.

stand up, rise up, make it through another day, uh.

can't stop me now, i've got so much to learn.

Chorus 1:

videography, documenting our rise,
no one can stop us, it's time to rise.

no matter what comes our way, we never give in to the chase.

boogity boobity, no sesame seeds in our tea.

with our bodies intertwined,
they hate and they can't resist,

Chorus 2:

Bridge:

all these hot tracks, make me a fan, it's only right.
no denying the fire in my heart,
feelin' fly in my jeans, ain't no need for all the fightin'.

Outro:
we'll walk together in this journey of life
while my left hand does the dash, moving forward with no strife.

now you look a little sad, your mind's a little numbing

ngelanga sifika kulomhlaba, i'll never forget it, boo.

and when we on that court, we ball so damn hard, we never tire.
got my trusty blues guitar, strummin' under the stars at night,

Chorus 1:

can't escape this love, it's my weakness.
not the soul, can't contain this bliss
all i can think about is you and me, so yummy with a kiss.

Verse 2:

climbing the stairway to heaven,
but finding happiness in a warm gun, instead.

Pre-Chorus 2:

and when you move slow, it's so alluring,

Chorus 2:

Bridge:

but i'll keep dreaming, tryna elevate my sum,
